BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Introduction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.0 Td (Sleep is not a luxury - it is a biological necessity. Poor sleep affects every system in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.0 Td (your body, from immune function and metabolism to mental health and cognitive performance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.0 Td (Yet one-third of adults do not get adequate sleep.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 638.2 Td (This workbook uses evidence-based Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Insomnia \(CBT-I\) - the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 624.2 Td (first-line treatment recommended by medical organizations - combined with comprehensive) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 610.2 Td (sleep hygiene optimization.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 582.4 Td (Who This Book Is For) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 566.4 Td (- People struggling to fall asleep or stay asleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.4 Td (- Anyone with chronic insomnia or poor sleep quality) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- Those wanting to optimize sleep for better health) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- People reducing or transitioning off sleep medications) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Shift workers, new parents, or those with disrupted schedules) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
