BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Sleep Science) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (The Two-Process Model of Sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Sleep is regulated by two systems working together:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 628.4 Td (Process S: Sleep Pressure \(Homeostatic\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612.4 Td (The longer you are awake, the stronger your drive to sleep. Adenosine accumulates in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 598.4 Td (brain during waking hours, creating 'sleep pressure.' Caffeine blocks adenosine receptors,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (which is why it keeps you awake.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 556.6 Td (Process C: Circadian Rhythm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 540.6 Td (Your internal 24-hour clock, controlled by the suprachiasmatic nucleus \(SCN\) in the brain.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 526.6 Td (Light exposure is the primary signal that sets this clock. Melatonin release begins in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 512.6 Td (evening as light decreases.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 482.8 Td (Sleep Architecture) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 460.8 Td (Sleep Stages) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 444.8 Td (- Stage 1 \(N1\): Light sleep, transition stage \(5% of night\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430.8 Td (- Stage 2 \(N2\): True sleep onset, memory consolidation \(45%\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 416.8 Td (- Stage 3 \(N3\): Deep/slow-wave sleep, physical restoration \(25%\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 402.8 Td (- REM Sleep: Dreaming, emotional processing, learning \(25%\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 379.0 Td (One complete sleep cycle takes 90-110 minutes. You need 4-6 cycles per night.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 349.2 Td (Consequences of Poor Sleep) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 327.2 Td (Short-Term \(1-3 nights\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 311.2 Td (- Impaired concentration and memory) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 297.2 Td (- Irritability and mood changes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 283.2 Td (- Increased appetite and cravings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 269.2 Td (- Reduced immune function) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 251.2 Td (Long-Term \(Chronic\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 235.2 Td (- Increased risk of obesity and diabetes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 221.2 Td (- Cardiovascular disease) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 207.2 Td (- Depression and anxiety) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 193.2 Td (- Cognitive decline and dementia risk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 179.2 Td (- Weakened immune system) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 165.2 Td (- Hormonal imbalances) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 135.4 Td (Common Causes of Insomnia) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 117.4 Td (- Hyperarousal: Racing mind, inability to 'turn off') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 103.4 Td (- Poor sleep habits: Irregular schedule, screen use) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 89.4 Td (- Anxiety and depression) Tj ET
endstream
