stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 3: CBT-I Techniques) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 680.2 Td (CBT-I is the gold standard treatment for chronic insomnia, recommended over medication by) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 666.2 Td (medical organizations worldwide. It addresses the root causes of insomnia rather than just) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 652.2 Td (masking symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 622.4 Td (Technique 1: Sleep Restriction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Counterintuitively, spending less time in bed improves sleep quality.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 590.4 Td (- Step 1: Calculate your average sleep time from diary \(e.g., 5.5 hours\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576.4 Td (- Step 2: Set your time in bed to that amount \(minimum 5 hours\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 562.4 Td (- Step 3: Choose a fixed wake time \(e.g., 6:30 AM\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548.4 Td (- Step 4: Calculate bedtime \(wake time minus sleep window\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- Step 5: When sleep efficiency reaches 85%+, add 15 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.6 Td (Sleep Efficiency = \(Total Sleep Time / Time in Bed\) x 100) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 482.8 Td (My Sleep Restriction Plan) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.8 Td (Current average sleep time: ___ hours) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.8 Td (Initial sleep window: ___ hours) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.8 Td (Fixed wake time: ___:___ AM) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424.8 Td (Initial bedtime: ___:___ PM) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 395.0 Td (Technique 2: Stimulus Control) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 377.0 Td (Break the association between bed/bedroom and wakefulness:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 363.0 Td (- Go to bed ONLY when sleepy \(not just tired\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 349.0 Td (- Use the bed only for sleep and intimacy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 335.0 Td (- If awake for 15-20 minutes, get up and do something calm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 321.0 Td (- Return to bed only when sleepy again) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.0 Td (- Wake at the same time every day regardless of sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 293.0 Td (- No napping during the day \(or limit to 20 min before 2pm\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 263.2 Td (Technique 3: Cognitive Restructuring) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 245.2 Td (Challenge unhelpful thoughts about sleep:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 217.4 Td (Common Sleep Myths to Challenge) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 201.4 Td (- Myth: 'I need exactly 8 hours or I can't function') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 187.4 Td (  Reality: Sleep needs vary \(6-9 hours\). Quality matters more than quantity.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 173.4 Td (- Myth: 'One bad night will ruin my whole week') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 159.4 Td (  Reality: Your body compensates with deeper sleep the following night.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 145.4 Td (- Myth: 'I should try harder to fall asleep') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 131.4 Td (  Reality: Effort is the enemy of sleep. Let go of trying.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 117.4 Td (- Myth: 'Lying in bed resting is almost as good as sleeping') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 103.4 Td (  Reality: Lying awake in bed creates conditioned arousal.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
