100 0 obj
<< /Length 3021 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: How long does CBT-I take to work?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Most people see improvement within 2-4 weeks. Full benefits are typically achieved in 6-8) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (weeks. It's normal for things to feel harder before they get better, especially with sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (restriction.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: Is it normal to feel worse when starting sleep restriction?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (Yes. Initial daytime sleepiness is expected and actually helps build stronger sleep drive.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (This temporary discomfort leads to better, more consolidated sleep.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 546.6 Td (Q: Should I take melatonin every night?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (Melatonin is best for circadian rhythm issues \(jet lag, shift work\) rather than general) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (insomnia. Long-term nightly use is not recommended. Discuss with your doctor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 488.8 Td (Q: Why does alcohol make insomnia worse?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (While alcohol helps you fall asleep initially, it severely disrupts sleep architecture,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (suppresses REM sleep, and causes middle-of-the-night awakenings as it metabolizes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 431.0 Td (Q: Can I ever catch up on lost sleep?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (Partially. One or two late mornings can help, but chronic sleep debt cannot be fully) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401.0 Td (repaid by sleeping in on weekends. Consistency is more important than marathon sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 387.0 Td (sessions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 359.2 Td (Q: When should I see a sleep specialist?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 343.2 Td (If insomnia persists after 4-6 weeks of CBT-I, or if you suspect sleep apnea \(snoring,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 329.2 Td (gasping, daytime sleepiness despite adequate hours\), excessive daytime sleepiness, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 315.2 Td (restless legs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 287.4 Td (Q: Is napping good or bad?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.4 Td (For insomnia sufferers, napping typically makes nighttime sleep worse by reducing sleep) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.4 Td (pressure. If you must nap, keep it under 20 minutes and before 2pm.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 229.6 Td (Q: Does screen time really affect sleep?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 213.6 Td (Yes. Blue light from screens suppresses melatonin production by up to 50%. The stimulating) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 199.6 Td (content also increases arousal. Stop screens 1+ hour before bed.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 171.8 Td (Q: What if I work shifts?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 155.8 Td (Shift workers need modified strategies: blackout curtains for day sleep, strategic light) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 141.8 Td (exposure, consistent anchor sleep times, and melatonin timed to your desired sleep window.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 114.0 Td (Q: Can anxiety cause insomnia?) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
101 0 obj
